docs.abstract: Low-cost options abound, giving investors with modest means access to choices once reserved for giants like pension funds.
docs.snippet: Low-cost options abound, giving investors with modest means access to choices once reserved for giants like pension funds.
docs.lead_paragraph: Fees on mutual funds and exchange-traded funds have been dropping so low that investors can now get the access and capabilities once enjoyed only by large institutions like pension funds at minimal cost.

docs.abstract: A large and largely unexpected decline in bond interest rates requires downshifting expectations for the future.
docs.snippet: A large and largely unexpected decline in bond interest rates requires downshifting expectations for the future.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bond interest rates were supposed to rise in 2019. They have dropped instead, showing how dangerous it can be to make investing decisions based on assumptions about the direction of interest rates.

headline.main: Bond Returns Have Been Spectacular. Don’t Count on a Sequel.
